# @ai-sdk/pixelart

The **PixelArt provider** for the [AI SDK](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs) enables pixel art image generation via the [PixelArt AI API](https://api.pixelart.ai).

## Setup

The PixelArt provider is available as the `@ai-sdk/pixelart` module. You can install it with

```bash
npm i @ai-sdk/pixelart
```

## Provider Instance

You can import the default provider instance `pixelArt` from `@ai-sdk/pixelart`:

```ts
import { pixelArt } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';
```

If you need a custom setup, you can import `createPixelArt` and create a provider instance with your settings:

```ts
import { createPixelArt } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';

const pixelArt = createPixelArt({
  apiKey: 'your-api-key', // defaults to PIXELART_API_KEY env var
  baseURL: 'https://api.pixelart.ai/v1', // optional custom base URL
});
```

## Image Models

You can create PixelArt image models using a provider instance:

```ts
const model = pixelArt('pixelart-v1');
```

### Image Generation

```ts
import { generateImage } from 'ai';
import { pixelArt } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';

const { image } = await generateImage({
  model: pixelArt('pixelart-v1'),
  prompt: 'A hero character wielding a sword in a fantasy dungeon',
  size: '512x512',
});
```

### Provider-Specific Options

PixelArt supports these additional options via `providerOptions.pixelart`:

| Option         | Type                            | Description                                         |
| -------------- | ------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------- |
| `style`        | `'pixel' \| 'retro' \| '8bit'` | The pixel art rendering style. Default: `'pixel'`.  |
| `pixelDensity` | `number` (1–64)                 | Pixels per block — higher = chunkier. Default: `8`. |

```ts
import { generateImage } from 'ai';
import { pixelArt } from '@ai-sdk/pixelart';

const { image } = await generateImage({
  model: pixelArt('pixelart-v1'),
  prompt: 'A spaceship flying through an asteroid field',
  size: '256x256',
  seed: 42,
  providerOptions: {
    pixelart: {
      style: 'retro',
      pixelDensity: 16,
    },
  },
});
```

## Documentation

Please check out the [PixelArt provider documentation](https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/providers/pixelart) for more information.

